      "level": 2,
      "text": "What the Goethe A1 Exam Checks"
    },
    {
      "id": "n21",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 20,
      "text": "Goethe-Zertifikat A1: Start Deutsch 1 confirms basic German skills at CEFR A1 for adults."
    },
    {
      "id": "n22",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 21,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Exam format and timing"
    },
    {
      "id": "n23",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 22,
      "text": "The exam has listening, reading, writing, and speaking sections. The speaking section is an oral group examination."
    },
    {
      "id": "n24",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 23,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Listening"
    },
    {
      "id": "n25",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 24,
      "text": "20 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n26",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 25,
      "text": "Short everyday conversations, telephone messages, and public announcements."
    },
    {
      "id": "n27",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 26,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Reading"
    },
    {
      "id": "n28",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 27,
      "text": "25 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n29",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 28,
      "text": "Short notes, advertisements, information signs, and notices."
    },
    {
      "id": "n30",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 29,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Writing"
    },
    {
      "id": "n32",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 30,
      "text": "Simple forms and a short personal text about an everyday situation."
    },
    {
      "id": "n33",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 31,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Speaking"
    },
    {
      "id": "n34",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 32,
      "text": "15 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n35",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 33,
      "text": "Self-introduction, everyday questions and answers, and simple requests."
    },
    {
      "id": "n36",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 34,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Best for"
    },
    {
      "id": "n37",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 35,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Basic German proof"
    },
    {
      "id": "n38",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 36,
      "text": "Useful when you need to show beginner German for simple everyday communication."
    },
    {
      "id": "n39",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 37,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Family reunification preparation"
    },
    {
      "id": "n40",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 38,
      "text": "Relevant when a spouse visa route asks for A1-level German proof. Confirm accepted certificates with the German mission."
    },
    {
      "id": "n41",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 39,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "How to use your practice time"
    },
    {
      "id": "n42",
      "type": "list",
      "order": 40,
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Personal information, family, shopping, work, school, and housing vocabulary."
        },
        {
          "text": "Forms, signs, short notes, slow listening, and simple public announcements."
        },
        {
          "text": "Speaking prompts for introductions, basic questions, answers, and requests."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "n43",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 41,
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Frequently Asked Questions"
    },
    {
      "id": "n44",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 42,
      "text": "Everything you need to know about the exam!"
    },
    {
      "id": "n45",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 43,
      "text": "A1 is commonly linked to basic German proof for spouse reunification, but the embassy or consulate decides acceptance and exemptions."
    },
    {
      "id": "n46",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 44,
      "text": "Yes. You should practise listening, reading, writing, and speaking instead of preparing vocabulary only."
    },
    {
      "id": "n47",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 45,
      "text": "Start with personal details, numbers, dates, simple forms, everyday notices, and short spoken answers."
    },
    {
      "id": "n48",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 46,
      "text": "Last reviewed: May 2026. This page is independent exam preparation. For official registration, fees, dates, and accepted certificate rules, check the exam provider and the institution or authority requesting your certificate."
    }
